
** TWO_TASK

  - The TWO TASK does not exist under Windows. Windows uses the *LOCAL*
    environment variable or a registry entry.

** Adding services

  - netmgr (>= 9.2.0)
  - netca  (>= 8.1.5)
  - netasst(>= 8.1.5)

** tnsping service (command)

  - Try to connect to the specified oracle service. It does not
    verify whether the database is alive. It only validates the
    entries in *listener.ora*.

** lsncrtl (command)

  - help
  - start
  - stop
  - status

** tnsnames.ora (file)

  - $TNS_ADMIN
  - $ORACLE_HOME/network/admin
  - /var/opt/oracle

** TAF

  - OracleNetTaf

** sqlnet.ora (file)

  - NAMES.DIRECTORY_PATH = (TNSNAMES,EZCONNECT)


  - NAMES.DEFAULT_DOMAIN = local

    Appends to each service name the string local. So usage of this
    parameter makes only sense if the database are in one domain.

  - SQLNET.AUTHENTICATION_SERVICES = (NTS

    Uses Windows NT native authentication.

  - SQLNET.CRYPTO_SEED

    Uses the Oracle advance net option.

  - TRACE_LEVEL_CLIENT = 16

  - SQLNET.EXPIRE_TIME

** Local Listener

  - init parameter: *local_listener*

  - listener aliases must be declared in the tnsnames.ora

** DB Links

  - The view v$dblink shows all the active db links.

<example>
SQL> create database link sand connect to 
     rms13 identified by rms13 using 'sand';
SQL> desc currencies@sand;
</example>

** EZCONNECT


   user/pwd@//host[:port]/sid

